{"questionId":"15592","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{1}{3}{x^3} + \\frac{3}{4}{x^2} - x - 1\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the gradient of the graph of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 2\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{2^2} + \\frac{3}{2} \\times 2 - 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for correct substitution of 2 in their derivative of the function.</p>\n<p>6&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)</strong><strong><em>(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from part (d).</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15592","referen